*[[10 December]] – [[Ace Kefford]], bass player
*[[12 December]] – [[Clive Bunker]], drummer ([[Jethro Tull (band)|Jethro Tull]], [[Electric Sun]], [[Solstice (UK progressive rock band)|Solstice]], and [[Aviator (British band)|Aviator]])
*[[14 December]] – [[Jane Birkin]], French-based actress and singer
*[[16 December]] – [[Trevor Pinnock]], harpsichordist and conductor
*[[29 December]] – [[Marianne Faithfull]], singer and actress

==Deaths==
*[[29 January]] – [[Sidney Jones (composer)|Sidney Jones]], conductor and composer, 84<ref>{{cite book|author=Alan Hyman|title=Sullivan and his satellites: a survey of English operettas 1860-1914|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1QoXAQAAIAAJ|date=1 January 1978|publisher=Chappell|isbn=978-0-903443-24-1|page=210}}</ref>
*[[20 February]] – [[Hugh Allen (conductor)|Hugh Allen]], organist and choral conductor, 76<ref>{{cite book|author1=Maggie Humphreys|author2=Robert Evans|title=Dictionary of Composers for the Church in Great Britain and Ireland|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WSLUAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA6|date=1 January 1997|publisher=A&C Black|isbn=978-0-7201-2330-2|pages=6}}</ref>
*[[13 March]] – [[Thomas Dunhill]], composer and music writer, 69<ref>{{cite book|author=Gerald Norris|title=A musical gazetteer of Great Britain & Ireland|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KcMXAQAAIAAJ|date=June 1981|publisher=David & Charles|isbn=978-0-7153-7845-8|page=74}}</ref>
*[[13 April]] – [[William Henry Bell|W. H. Bell]], composer and conductor, 72<ref>{{cite book|author1=Maggie Humphreys|author2=Robert Evans|title=Dictionary of Composers for the Church in Great Britain and Ireland|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WSLUAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA28|date=1 January 1997|publisher=A&C Black|isbn=978-0-7201-2330-2|pages=28}}</ref>
*[[1 May]]
**[[Edward Bairstow]], organist and composer, 71<ref>{{cite book|author=Melvin P. Unger|title=Historical Dictionary of Choral Music|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SvD9Ou7wdccC&pg=PA27|date=17 June 2010|publisher=Scarecrow Press|isbn=978-0-8108-7392-6|pages=27}}</ref>
**[[Percy Whitlock]], organist and composer, 42 (tuberculosis)<ref>{{cite book|author=David Mason Greene|title=Greene's Biographical Encyclopedia of Composers|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=m3S7PIxe0mwC&pg=PA1329|year=1985|publisher=Reproducing Piano Roll Fnd.|isbn=978-0-385-14278-6|pages=1329}}</ref>
*[[16 October]] – Sir [[Granville Bantock]], composer, 78<ref>{{cite book|author=Jürgen Schaarwächter|title=Two Centuries of British Symphonism: From the beginnings to 1945. A preliminary survey. With a foreword by Lewis Foreman. Volume 1|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EIvoCQAAQBAJ&pg=PA510|date=27 February 2015|publisher=Georg Olms Verlag|isbn=978-3-487-15227-1|pages=510}}</ref>
*[[10 November]] – [[Nicholas Gatty]], composer and music critic, 72
*[[5 December]] – [[Tom Clare]], music hall singer and pianist, 70
*[[15 December]] – [[Frederic Norton]], composer, 77

